1. Definitions

"Software" means the source code, documentation, examples, demo files, and
other materials made available in this repository under this license.

"Licensor" means Philippos Zachiridis. Current licensor notice details are
listed in the NOTICE file distributed with this Software.

"You" means any person or legal entity receiving, using, modifying, deploying,
or distributing the Software.

"KBeam-Compatible Login" means the login flow implemented by the Software that
allows a waiting website or protected application to be unlocked by the KBeam
wallet application through the KBeam auth protocol.

"KBeam Compatibility Specification" means the versioned technical compatibility
document distributed with this Software as KBEAM-COMPATIBILITY.md, or a clear
successor document distributed with a later version of the Software. A copy,
fork, deployment, modified version, derivative work, hosted source release, or
substantial continuation is governed by the compatibility specification
included with the version it uses, unless Licensor separately authorizes
different compatibility terms in writing.

"Protected Compatibility Identifiers" means the identifiers required for
KBeam-Compatible Login, including:

- the challenge opening line "KBeam login"
- the protocol identifier "kbeam-auth-v1"
- the KBeam app URI scheme "kbeam://", including login routes under that
  scheme
- KBeam auth configuration and integration identifiers beginning with
  "KBEAM" or "kbeam" when they are used to preserve KBeam auth compatibility
- any additional protected identifiers listed in the KBeam Compatibility
  Specification distributed with this Software

"Minimum Compatibility Requirements" means that any copy, fork, deployment,
modified version, derivative work, hosted source release, or substantial
continuation that includes or is based on the KBeam-Compatible Login flow must
maintain a fully functional KBeam-Compatible Login path. At minimum, that path
must provide:

- a login challenge whose first line is "KBeam login"
- support for the protocol identifier "kbeam-auth-v1"
- an app approval URI compatible with the "kbeam://" scheme
- challenge creation that allows the KBeam wallet application to obtain the
  login challenge for a pending ticket
- approval handling that accepts a KBeam wallet signature for that challenge
- a waiting-browser status path, such as polling, SSE, or an equivalent event
  mechanism, that lets the protected website learn that the KBeam approval
  succeeded
- session or authorization handoff behavior that lets the protected website
  unlock for the browser that requested the login
- compatibility tests or equivalent verification procedures that exercise the
  KBeam-Compatible Login flow after material changes and before public
  deployment or redistribution
- license or notice materials that preserve the Protected Compatibility
  Identifiers and state that KBeam-compatible login must remain available
- compliance with the KBeam Compatibility Specification distributed with this
  Software

